LISTERIOSIS - CANADA: BACKGROUND
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Listeria contamination advisory - Canada (Quebec) 981119000642
Date: Thu, 19 Nov 1998 10:49:39 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on listeriosis in Canada were extracted from
the GIDEON software program:
An outbreak in Halifax in 1981 involved 41 cases (17 fatal) and was traced
to coleslaw.
Year Cases reported
1990 50
1992 32
1993 56 48 from Ontario
1994 47 35 from Ontario
1995 54 44 from Ontario
1997 33
1998 17 (January to June)
